The plan for "Dinner and a Show" is to help planning an eventing's activities (whether a date night, family vacation, etc).

Unfortunately after about 1-2 months of development on this project, Google released Google Local which has access to better data feeds for restaurants and attractions.  From an end user experience, I would recommend trying Google Local.  For the development knowledge, this project can still be very useful and hopefully I can add more features to make it more useful for everyone.

To use this source code, you need to get your own API keys for Factual, Pearson, New York Times, and Patch and put them in the ApiKeys.h file.

Some of the icons came from the Glyphish - http://glyphish.com/
